Pick n Pay is piloting a new packaging-free zone at its Constantia store in Cape Town. The retailer says that the zone will provide customers with the opportunity to purchase a wide range of products without packaging. The new zone includes 88 dry grocery products across 15 different categories including dry baking goods, cereals, dried fruit, flour, grains, ground coffee beans, nuts, pasta, pulses and beans, rice, seeds, spices, superfoods, olive oil and vinegar. Each category will have a range of products, including gluten-free options. Customers are encouraged to bring their own reusable container, but for those who forget, the store will offer free paper bags and a range of reusable containers that can be purchased. <img class="wp-image-359312 size-large aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-1-1024x605.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="496" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-1-1024x605.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-1-300x177.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-1-768x453.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-1-1536x907.jpg 1536w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-1-1200x708.jpg 1200w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-1.jpg 1980w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-359314 size-large" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-2-1024x742.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="609" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/