 that no new packaging is used in delivering the items to the store. During the trial, Pick n Pay hopes to identify the top 20 or 30 products and roll out packaging-free zones to more stores across the country. “We will closely monitor customer appetite for this offering and based on their feedback, will decide how to expand this offering. While all items are non-perishable with a naturally long shelf life, food waste is still a concern because without packaging, products will have a shorter shelf life,” Disberry said. <img class="wp-image-359318 size-large aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-4-1024x800.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="656" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-4-1024x800.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-4-300x234.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-4-768x600.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-4-1536x1200.jpg 1536w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-4-1200x937.jpg 1200w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-4.jpg 1549w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="wp-image-359320 size-large aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-5-1024x476.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="390" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-5-1024x476.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-5-300x140.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-5-768x357.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-5-1536x714.jpg 1536w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-5-1200x558.jpg 1200w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/PnP-packaging-free-zone-trial-Constantia-5.jpg 1873w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> Disberry saids customers will embrace the opportunity to purchase packaging-free products, judging by the positive reaction to the ‘nude’ fruit and vegetable produce wall trial Pick n Pay ran in July to measure customers’ readiness to switch from pre-packaged food to loose products. “The number of stores offering customers a ‘nude’ fruit and vegetable produce wall has more than doubled since our trial launched, from just 13 stores to 29. “Stores have also extended the range to offer 24 seasonal loose PnP fruit and vegetables, up from 12 products. At this special section in the store, free paper bags are provided or customers can purchase a PnP reusable netted fresh-produce bags (R7,50) or bring their own clear and sealable container,” said Disberry. Read: Pick n Pay is now offering insurance 